
Read these instructions before disregarding them.
To install Brainix:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extract the source:
	 Type: tar xfvz Brainix-YYYY-MM-DD.tar.gz
	 Type: cd Brainix-0.0

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Edit include/config.h (if necessary):
	 This should be self-explanatory.  If it isn't, just skip it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Edit GNUmakefile (if necessary):
	 Modify FDDEV to point to your floppy device.
	 Modify FDMNT to point to your floppy mount point.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Compile:
	 Type: make clean
	 Type: make

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Create a boot disk:
	 Insert a disk into your floppy drive.
	 As root, type: make floppy

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Boot:
	 Boot from the disk created in the previous step.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If something goes wrong, then email any member of Team Brainix with a detailed
description of your problem.  (Email addresses are provided in: doc/credits)
We'll reply as quickly as we can.

Happy hacking!  :-)
Team Brainix

